Czech Stocks: Central European Media, CEZ, Erste Move in Prague

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-09-15T09:20:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/czech-stocks-central-european-media-cez-erste-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s PX stock index
rose 1 percent to 954.4 as of 11 a.m. in Prague, ending a four-
day decline.  The following are among the most active equities on the
Prague Stock Exchange today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Central European Media Enterprises Ltd. (CETV)   rose 5.8
percent to 187.4 koruna, heading for its biggest one-day
increase in three weeks. The broadcaster was upgraded to “buy”
from “accumulate” at Ceska Sporitelna AS.  CEZ AS (CEZ)   fell 0.8 percent to 761 koruna, ending a
two-day advance. The largest Czech power utility earlier slid as
much as 1.6 percent after Chief Executive Officer Martin Roman
unexpectedly announced he was leaving the post.  Erste Group Bank AG (EBS)   climbed 1.8 percent to 500
koruna, snapping a five-day decline. The Austrian lender said
yesterday it reached an agreement to buy a 24.1 percent stake in
Banca Comerciala Romana SA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in  Prague  at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  